 my new room.

But suddenly I slapped my brow and burst out laughing. How simple it all was! How simply, said I to myself, the mysterious frenzy of that letter has now been solved. A proprietor’s frenzy! Ardalion cannot forgive my having taken his name for cipher and staging the murder on his strip of earth. He is mistaken; all are gone bankrupt long ago; nobody knows whom this earth really belongs to—and … Ah, enough, enough about my fool Ardalion! The ultimate dab is laid on his portrait